**Full Text**: Google didn't fall in love with Reddit. It followed the users.

People have been appending "reddit" to searches for years because they wanted answers that felt earned, not optimized. After the May 2026 core update, Reddit's No. 1 rankings jumped 54%.

That's the B2B signal. Google is separating "needs expertise" from "needs experience." Your buyers need both.

Run this check. Search your category, brand, and top competitors with "reddit" added. Look at pricing, onboarding, and switching stories.

If Reddit says implementation is painful and your homepage says "launch in minutes," buyers are already noticing.

Stop treating Reddit as a side channel. It's buyer research, reputation monitoring, and content strategy in one place.

